[h1]Shamans[/h1]
Shamans have a powerful bond with the spirit world and use it to strengthen their allies and summon powerful elementals.

[h1]Special Features[/h1]
[h2]Local Elementals[/h2]
Shamans are highly dependent on their surroundings. Their spells are influenced by which elemental spirits are present nearby; presence varies by place and affects both [section:clr-mp]MP[/section] cost and damage type. If there is no presence at all, the spell cannot be cast. Certain consumables (e.g., elemental cores) can substitute for natural sources.
[h3]Presence & MP costs[/h3]
Costs are written [i]weak[/i]/[i]normal[/i]/[i]strong[/i]. Example: [section:clr-mp]3/2/1 MP[/section] means costs drop from [section:clr-value]3[/section] (weak presence) to [section:clr-value]1[/section] (strong presence).
[h3]Environmental Preferences[/h3]
Elemental spirits are drawn to concentrations of their element. [b]Examples:[/b]
[h4]Water[/h4]
[b]Weak:[/b] bucket/puddle/mist
[br][b]Normal:[/b] brook/pond/rain
[br][b]Strong:[/b] river/ocean/lake/downpour
[h4]Stone[/h4]
[b]Weak:[/b] soil/hill
[br][b]Normal:[/b] rock floor/boulders
[br][b]Strong:[/b] cave/mountains
[h4]Fire[/h4]
[b]Weak:[/b] torch
[br][b]Normal:[/b] campfire
[br][b]Strong:[/b] wildfire/volcano
[h4]Air[/h4]
[b]Weak:[/b] breeze
[br][b]Normal:[/b] strong wind
[br][b]Strong:[/b] storm

[h1]Foci[/h1]
Shaman foci are usually amulets adorned with elementally significant symbols, or staffs with inlet elemental cores.

[h1]Proficiency Values[/h1]
[h3]Binding[/h3]
Each point in [i]Binding[/i] increases [section:clr-dc]DC[/section] of [i]Binding[/i] spells [url:core#Eased]eases[/url] Concentration checks for [i]Binding[/i] spells by [section:clr-value]1[/section].
[h3]Summoning[/h3]
Each point in [i]Summoning[/i] increases the [section:clr-sa]SA[/section] of [i]Summoning[/i] spells, damage from [i]Summoning[/i] spells, and damage from summoned elementalsâ€™ attacks by [section:clr-value]1[/section].

[h1]Spell Upgrades[/h1]
Shaman spells can be upgraded for [section:clr-value]4 SP[/section] to the equivalent of the next spell tier. You may still use the lower-tier version afterward.